    "lp_faq": {
      "type": "aliange-lp-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "q1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What makes the Anti-Ageing Protocol different from using individual products?",
            "answer": "<p>This protocol is designed as a <strong>complete, structured system</strong>, not a collection of standalone products.<br/><br/>Each step targets a different biological pathway of ageing—collagen degradation, pigmentation, barrier decline, and cellular turnover—so the skin is treated <strong>across a full 24-hour cycle, not in isolation</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What skin concerns does the Anti-Ageing Protocol address?",
            "answer": "<p>The protocol is formulated to target the primary drivers of visible ageing:</p><ul><li><br/>Fine lines and loss of firmness<br/></li><li><br/>Uneven skin tone and pigmentation<br/></li><li><br/>Dehydration and dullness<br/></li><li><br/>Collagen and elastin breakdown<br/></li><li><br/>Environmental and UV-related damage</li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "question_JwcV8d": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I use this protocol if I’m new to active skincare?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. This protocol is specifically designed to <strong>guide the skin through actives in a controlled sequence</strong>.</p><p>Unlike random product use, each step is calibrated to:</p><ul><li><br/>Prepare the skin<br/></li><li><br/>Deliver actives<br/></li><li><br/>Support recovery<br/></li></ul><p>This reduces the risk of irritation commonly seen with unsupervised retinol or acid use.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does the protocol actually improve ageing skin?",
            "answer": "<p>Rather than relying on a single mechanism, the protocol works through <strong>multi-pathway correction</strong>:</p><ul><li><br/><strong>Retinoid renewal</strong> → stimulates cellular turnover and collagen production<br/></li><li><br/><strong>Peptide signalling</strong> → supports dermal structure and elasticity<br/></li><li><br/><strong>Acid resurfacing</strong> → refines texture and accelerates epidermal renewal<br/></li><li><br/><strong>Barrier repair + hydration</strong> → improves tolerance and skin function<br/></li></ul><p>This layered approach reflects how ageing occurs biologically—<strong>not as one issue, but as multiple systems declining simultaneously</strong>.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_ffXMCq": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will this replace in-clinic treatments?",
            "answer": "<p>This protocol is designed to:</p><ul><li><br/><strong>Enhance and maintain clinical results</strong><br/></li><li><br/>Improve skin quality between treatments<br/></li><li><br/>Reduce the rate of ongoing deterioration<br/></li></ul><p>It can significantly improve skin function, but also works synergistically with in-clinic procedures.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_V8PnB6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is this safe during pregnancy or breastfeeding?",
            "answer": "<p>Some steps—particularly those containing <strong>retinoids or active exfoliants</strong>—are not recommended during pregnancy or breastfeeding.</p><p>Always consult your healthcare provider and refer to individual product guidance.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_fDHth3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I combine this with other Aliangé protocols?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes.</p><p>The Anti-Ageing Protocol can be integrated with:</p><ul><li><br/><strong>Masque Protocol</strong> (weekly correction and resurfacing)<br/></li><li><br/><strong>Barrier or repair protocols</strong> if skin is compromised<br/></li></ul><p>Protocols are designed to <strong>layer intelligently across time</strong>, not compete.</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_Nwq4bR": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do I need to use every step for results?",
            "answer": "<p>For optimal outcomes, yes.</p><p>Each step performs a distinct function:</p><ul><li><br/>Removing one step reduces the system’s ability to <strong>fully correct and maintain results</strong><br/></li></ul><p>However, the protocol can be adjusted based on tolerance or lifestyle if needed.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long does it take to see results?",
            "answer": "<ul><li><strong>2–4 weeks:</strong> improved hydration, clarity, and skin texture<br/></li><li><br/><strong>8–12 weeks:</strong> visible improvements in tone, firmness, and fine lines<br/></li><li><br/><strong>12+ weeks:</strong> structural changes in skin quality and resilience <br/></li></ul><p>Skin responds to <strong>consistent signalling over time</strong>, not short-term intensity.</p>"
          }
        },
        "q5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is this suitable for sensitive or reactive skin?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes—with structured introduction.</p><p>The protocol is designed to <strong>support tolerance</strong>, not overwhelm the skin.<br/><br/>Barrier-supportive ingredients are layered alongside actives to minimise irritation.</p><p>For highly reactive skin:</p><ul><li><br/>Begin with reduced frequency (e.g. alternate nights for retinoid)<br/></li><li><br/>Always patch test prior to full use<br/></li></ul>"
          }
        }
